	(168,1,'2016-09-23 14:29:43','2016-09-23 14:29:43','<a href=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/10-8-14.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Here is the letter</a> sent on Wednesday, October 8, by Charles A. Baker, secretary for Sterling Suffolk Racecourse, LLC (Suffolk Downs), to the Massachusetts Gaming Commission.\r\n\r\nIn addition to the letter, Suffolk Downs has issued the following statement:\r\n\r\n\"On behalf of our workers and the horsemen and women here, we felt an obligation to raise these issues to the Gaming Commission, especially in light of new information regarding the Everett land and the continuing questions around the suitability of individuals associated with that land. We are asking the commission to re-examine incurable defects in this process that prevent the Everett proposal from complying with the law.\"\r\n\r\nSuffolk Downs COO, Chip Tuttle','Letter From Charles A. Baker, Secretary For Sterling Suffolk Racecourse, LLC To The Massachusetts Gaming Comission','','publish','closed','open','','letter-from-charles-a-baker-secretary-for-sterling-suffolk-racecourse-llc-to-the-massachusetts-gaming-commission','','','2016-09-23 14:49:03','2016-09-23 14:49:03','',0,'http://suffolk.dev:8888/?p=168',0,'post','',0),
